<html>
  <problem>
    
      <p>Ball A is dropped from the top of a building.  One second later, ball B is dropped from the same building. Consider the balls while they are both in flight.  You may ignore air resistance.  Which statements are true about this situation?</p>
    
    <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" max="10" randomize="yes" loncapaid="11">
      <ul>
        <conceptgroup concept="One">
          <optioninput location="random" name="OneA" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                Both have the same vertical acceleration
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="OneB" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                Both have a horizontal acceleration of zero
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="OneC" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                Both are under the influence of gravity only
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="OneD" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

Both are in free fall
              
              <br/>

        </conceptgroup>
        <conceptgroup concept="Two">
          <optioninput location="random" name="TwoA" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                As time progresses, the distance between them increases
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="TwoB" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                As time progresses, the distance between them stays constant
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="TwoC" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

As time progresses, the distance between them decreases
              
              <br/>

        </conceptgroup>
        <conceptgroup concept="Three">
          <optioninput location="random" name="ThreeA" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                As time progresses, the difference between their velocities increases
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="ThreeB" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                As time progresses, the difference between their velocities decreases
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="ThreeC" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

As time progresses, the difference between their velocities stays the same
              
              <br/>

        </conceptgroup>
        <conceptgroup concept="Four">
          <optioninput location="random" name="FourA" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                As time progresses, the difference between their accelerations increases
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FourB" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

                As time progresses, the difference between their accelerations decreases
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FourC" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

As time progresses, the difference between their accelerations stays the same
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FourD" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

The difference between their accelerations is always zero
              
              <br/>

        </conceptgroup>
        <conceptgroup concept="">
          <optioninput location="random" name="FiveA" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

Ball A will hit the ground before ball B
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FiveB" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

Ball B will hit the ground after ball A
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FiveC" correct="True" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

Both balls will hit the ground with the same speed
              
              <br/>

          <optioninput location="random" name="FiveD" correct="False" options="('True','False')"></optioninput>

Both balls will hit the ground simultaneously
              
              <br/>

        </conceptgroup>
      </ul>
      <hintgroup showoncorrect="no">
        
          <p>Add hint text here.</p>
        
      </hintgroup>
    </optionresponse>
  </problem>
</html>
